</i></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=targok>Targok</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/3/03 10:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2152.topic&index=31>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_cooldude.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Hmph</span><hr size=1> Yeah, 12 hours into Xenogears and you haven't even scratched the surface.<br>
Ridiculous that it builds that slow? Perhaps.<br>
The pay-off was worth it though. Almost all RPG material is kiddy stuff compared to the depths this game goes to.<br>
<br>
As far as dialogue in previous FFs.. while there wasn't massive amounts of text, it wasn't necessary. Sure, RPGs have made a technical leap, but they've regressed in the ability to tell a cohesive story and create intriguing characters. The characters in VII were horrible. But I dunno what people are looking for in characterization, because most people seem to enjoy the mindnumbing stereotypes that were prevelant in it.<br>
<br>
Final Fantasies were always epic in scope, and always had a &quot;cinematic&quot; presentation. Square tried to raise the bar with VII, by upping the cinematic value and visual appeal, at the expense of cohesive storytelling and likeable characters. Unfortunately, the formula worked, and now the cinematic aspect of the game is heavily favored over the actual meat of the game.<br>
<br>
You know what the most enjoyable RPG I played in years was?<br>
Golden Sun for the GBA. Nifty gameplay coupled w/ a logical story. Cliche, yes, but executed nicely. Had just enough wimsy to make it *fun* to play. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=deldrach>Deldrach</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/4/03 2:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2152.topic&index=32>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_cooldude.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re:</span><hr size=1> I must have downloaded practically every single SNES Rom I ever remembered playing. Having gone back an fiddled with many of them it is just shocking how boring most of the old games are now that we are so spoiled as gamers. I can count on 1 hand the number of old console games that I can actually enjoy playing again for more than 5 minutes. FFVI is certainly at the very top of the list. In fact, I must have played through it about 20+ times. My brain pretty much contains a virtual walkthrough.<br>
<br>
The funny thing is I know I am most certainly not alone in this sentiment. About a year ago FFOnline.com, the largest final fantasy fan website on the net did a massive survey of gamers to rank their top 25 favorite Squaresoft games of all time. FFVI beat out FFVII and headlined the list. The fact that despite being almost 10 years old, so many people still take enjoyment from FFVI certainly says something for it standing the test of time. Not too shabby...<br>
<br>
On a final note, I did like FFVII as well, but I would still rather fire up my FFVI Rom any day of the week.<br>
<br>
Oh, and Suikoden II &gt; Xenogears <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=targok>Targok</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/4/03 3:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2152.topic&index=33>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_cooldude.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Re:</span><hr size=1> FF VI had the perfect mix. Compelling story, characters, gameplay, all backed by a great score.<br>
